      • ID3v23FrameBodySynchronizedTempoCodes.TempoChange

        public ID3v23FrameBodySynchronizedTempoCodes.TempoChange(int beatsPerMinute,
                                                 int timeStamp)
        constructor used to create a tempo change.
        Parameters:
        beatsPerMinute - 0 indicates a beat-free time period. 1 indicates a single beat-stroke followed by a beat-free period. 2 - 510 indicates the metronome setting for the song, ie, the number of beats per minute.
        timeStamp - the timestamp in the song where the tempo change occurs. The units of the timestamp are specified by the time stamp format field.
